      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FASCINATE OLIVER (1) has missed the frame at his last two but did run well three back when third (17.74) in a Grade 5 at Taree Super Track. Key player on best and expected to bounce back. CHAMPAGNE BLISS (6) finished in the money two back then was well fancied latest and led into the straight but ran over, finishing second (16.01) at this track in a Grade 4/5. Has never been out of the money in three starts this course. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Ready to find winning form. MINTER MULWEE (8) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (23.44) at this track behind Lochinvar Grace in a Grade 5. Has the pace to be prominent. Leading chance. DON'T DO IT (7) can run a bold race on best form.",
